A '''heart tree''' is the center of a [[Godswood]]. It is a [[Weirwood]] tree that has a face carved into the wood of the trunk. Heart trees are sacred in the religion of the [[Old Gods of the Forest]], and the closest thing to a &quot;shrine&quot; that the religion possesses.

Weirwoods have red sap, which leaks out of the deep cuts in the trunk made for the eyes of the faces - giving the appearance that they are weeping tearsÂ of blood. The faces are thought to have been carved by the [[Children of the Forest]].&lt;ref name=&quot;VG Dawn Age&quot;&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/guide/appendix/beyond-the-houses/ HBO Viewer's Guide, Season 2 appendices, Westeros Through the Ages - Dawn Age entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
